  "title": "Massage Therapist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Client Consultation & Assessment:</strong> Discuss symptoms, medical history, and goals to create personalized treatment plans.</li><li><strong>Massage Techniques:</strong> Apply pressure to soft tissues (muscles, tendons, ligaments) using hands, fingers, or forearms to improve circulation and relieve tension.</li><li><strong>Specialized Care:</strong> Perform various modalities, including deep tissue, prenatal, sports, and hot stone massage.</li><li><strong>Health Education:</strong> Instruct clients on stretching, strengthening, and posture improvement techniques.</li><li><strong>Record Keeping & Hygiene:</strong> Maintain accurate, confidential client records and sanitize equipment/rooms.</li><li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Work with chiropractors, physiotherapists, or physicians for patient rehabilitation. </li></ul><p><strong>Required Skills & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Certification/Licensure:</strong> Completion of a state-approved, accredited massage therapy program and proper licensing/registration.</li><li><strong>Physical Stamina:</strong> Ability to stand for long periods and perform strenuous, repetitive manual work.</li><li><strong>Interpersonal Skills:</strong> Strong communication and listening skills to understand client needs and build rapport.</li><li><strong>Knowledge of Anatomy:</strong> Strong understanding of human body mechanics, muscles, and tissues. </li></ul>",
